README.md:97:- Two enhancement lanes currently wear **"floors not met — experimental"** labels (reference retrieval E2, entity resolution E4): their pre-registered quality bars were missed on the one permitted scoring pass, the misses are published in full, and re-attempts require fresh registered splits. Deferred is a result here, not a failure mode to hide.
docs/GLOSSARY.md:38:| **Entity-resolution lane (E4)** | The advisory fuzzy name-matcher (`lib/entity/`): a similarity ensemble (Jaro-Winkler · token-set · phonetic) over the frozen A2 normalization chain, proposing SAME / DIFFERENT / ABSTAIN under two pre-registered thresholds. Advisory-never-gating: nothing in the engine imports it, exact matching remains the protected default, and its scoring against pre-registered floors (one pass, synthetic adversarial corpus) is published in its registration doc's RESULTS. | The "are these two messy names the same business?" helper. It only ever suggests; when unsure it hands the question to a human; and the exact-match rule it failed to beat is still the one the system actually uses. |
