VERDICT: REVISE

1. P1 — E4 scored a corpus that violated the frozen trap-case minimum. The original preregistration requires at least 12 near-miss traps ([preregistration](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/docs/e4-entity-resolution-preregistration.md:53)); the tightening amendment does not weaken that requirement ([preregistration](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/docs/e4-entity-resolution-preregistration.md:97)). The generator produced only 10, while the composition gate checked only the amendment’s weaker ≥8 denominator floor ([generator](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/scripts-ts/generate-entity-corpus.mts:203), [composition test](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/evals/entity/entity-corpus-composition.test.ts:44)). Results then reported 10 as compliant ([preregistration results](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/docs/e4-entity-resolution-preregistration.md:116)). The exposed E4 run is not a preregistration-compliant exam; it cannot support the claimed one-pass evaluation without a fresh registered split.

2. P1 — E2 M5 was graded under post-gold semantics that contradict the registered grader. A4 requires markers absent from every output field ([preregistration](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/docs/e2-rag-preregistration.md:155)); the gold file makes this “the full serialized LaneResult” ([adversarial-inserts.json](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/evals/rag/gold/adversarial-inserts.json:2)). The harness serializes the full results and then discards that value, checking only `answered`, `answer_span`, and citation filenames ([rag-score.mts](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/scripts-ts/rag-score.mts:158)). The lock repeats the narrowed rule ([rag-results-lock.test.ts](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/evals/rag/rag-results-lock.test.ts:65)). Under the registered full-output rule, retrieved poison markers appear in hits/citation spans, so the published 1/3 and 2/3 valid-clean counts are wrong; both are 0/3. The overall deferred label remains correct, but the committed metric and “markers absent 6/6” claim do not.

3. P1 — E3 signatures do not bind the action, case, or expiry being executed. The signed payload omits `caseId`, `action`, `requestedAtMs`, and `expiresAtMs` ([types.ts](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/lib/approvals/types.ts:83), [simulator.ts](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/lib/approvals/simulator.ts:97)). Verification trusts the unsigned expiry and emits unsigned case/action fields into the execution record ([simulator.ts](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/lib/approvals/simulator.ts:135), [simulator.ts](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/lib/approvals/simulator.ts:182)). A read-only exploit probe changed a signed request’s case, action, and expiry; all seven checks passed and returned `executed: true` with the altered values. The suite attacks decision tampering only ([threat-model.test.ts](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/evals/approvals/threat-model.test.ts:136)). This defeats the signed-action, expiry, and “exactly what was reviewed” guarantees.

4. P1 — E2’s A1 hard block is not independently anchored to the preregistration. `assertCorpusPins` trusts caller-provided hashes ([blob-hash.ts](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/lib/rag/blob-hash.ts:55)); runtime and tests both obtain those hashes from the mutable manifest ([corpus.ts](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/lib/rag/corpus.ts:23), [corpus-manifest.test.ts](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/evals/rag/corpus-manifest.test.ts:26)). Only one of 82 hashes is independently hardcoded in the tests ([corpus-manifest.test.ts](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/evals/rag/corpus-manifest.test.ts:36)); the other top-level blobs and registered schema-tree hash are not. Snapshot and manifest can therefore be changed together while the “hard-block” suite remains green. The current 82 snapshot files do match the original pins, but the claimed future tamper gate is self-referential.

5. P1 — The frozen E2 manifest/loader changed after scoring without a committed reversal. The manifest says it must not change after gold access ([corpus-manifest.json](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/lib/rag/corpus-manifest.json:1)), yet `d432fa4` changed it and redirected the only loader to a new snapshot root ([corpus.ts](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/lib/rag/corpus.ts:30)). The change preserves current bytes and does not imply rescoring, but it violates the packet’s “freeze edits only via recorded reversal” hard stop. No reversal row exists in committed `HEAD`; a decision-log row appeared uncommitted during this review and cannot retroactively satisfy the gate.

6. P2 — The asserted preregistration byte boundary and chain are inaccurate. `git diff 31bd66d..HEAD` adds both documents’ amendments above their `RESULTS` markers. Those amendments actually landed in `ff4181e`, before index/corpus work, so there is no evidence of post-scoring goalpost movement; however, the operative chains must include `ff4181e`, and only `ff4181e..HEAD` is unchanged above the markers. The requested “byte-unchanged versus 31bd66d” confirmation is false.

7. P2 — E4 threshold tuning lacks physical test isolation. The tuner does not access `corpus.test` in its calculations, but it reads and parses the single JSON file containing both tune and test before selecting `.tune` ([tune-entity-thresholds.mts](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/scripts-ts/tune-entity-thresholds.mts:18)). Thus the commit claim that test data was “never read by tuning code” is literally false, even though no test-derived computation was found.

8. P2 — Embedding provenance is recorded but not enforced. The fetch script separately reads the current HF revision, while `pipeline()` downloads `main` without that revision ([rag-fetch-model.mts](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/scripts-ts/rag-fetch-model.mts:31)). Offline inference loads by model ID without validating the manifest’s revision or cached-file hashes ([embed-transformers.ts](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/lib/rag/embed-transformers.ts:29)). Tests validate only hash formatting ([corpus-manifest.test.ts](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/evals/rag/corpus-manifest.test.ts:96)). Network denial proves “no fetch,” not that scoring used the provenance-pinned model bytes.

9. P2 — E3’s no-send/no-mutation regression proof is incomplete. Its denylist covers selected packages and built-ins but permits filesystem writes, unlisted mail/Slack/network clients, database clients, and other mutation paths ([no-send-import-graph.test.ts](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/evals/approvals/no-send-import-graph.test.ts:54)). Bare packages are not traversed ([no-send-import-graph.test.ts](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/evals/approvals/no-send-import-graph.test.ts:29)). The present graph is clean, but the test does not enforce the full promised threat class.

10. P2 — E1b reconciliation remains internally inconsistent.

   - The payload does not carry the preregistered deferred label verbatim despite comments claiming it does ([lookup-reference.ts](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/lib/tools/tools/lookup-reference.ts:7), [lookup-reference.ts](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/lib/tools/tools/lookup-reference.ts:33)).
   - GLOSSARY still says MCP/registry expose six tools, contradicting the seven-tool registry and SHOWCASE ([GLOSSARY.md](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/docs/GLOSSARY.md:52)).
   - Every E4 matcher result carries “entity resolution validated…” after the mandatory floors-not-met outcome ([matcher.ts](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/lib/entity/matcher.ts:44)).
   - New E2/E4 dashboard provenance uses prose instead of the required freezing SHA, and the provenance test omits these objects ([evidence.ts](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/lib/dashboard/evidence.ts:262), [dashboard-evidence.test.ts](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/evals/packs/dashboard-evidence.test.ts:180)).

11. P3 — E3’s promised single-line audit record permits newline injection. Request creation does not constrain `caseId` or nonce characters ([simulator.ts](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/lib/approvals/simulator.ts:65)), while the audit line interpolates raw identifiers ([simulator.ts](/Users/sharan_98/Desktop/curbside-commons/lib/approvals/simulator.ts:196)). A newline-bearing case ID produced a three-line record.

Confirmed non-findings:

- No evidence of a second E2/E4 scoring artifact or results commit.
- E2’s BM25 parameters remained frozen; density hardening preceded scoring.
- E2’s M2 artifact disclosure is honest and was not post-hoc regraded.
- E4 raw arithmetic, determinism, zero-denominator handling, deferred label, and baseline tie were independently confirmed.
- Runtime `lookup_reference` is BM25-only; no Transformers import is reachable from the registry path.
- `legacy/` and top-level `fixtures/` diffs are empty; exactly the six declared existing eval files were modified.
- Both raw seat-death messages and NO-WAIT conversions are present in commit messages.
- Replay-before-signature does not burn nonces; the implemented seven-check order matches its documentation.

Validation limitation: Vitest could not collect tests because the read-only sandbox denied its temporary-directory creation (`EPERM`). Therefore the README’s `1130 passed + 7 skipped` count was not independently rerun. The worktree also acquired an unrelated uncommitted `docs/decision-log.md` change during review; it was not made by this reviewer or treated as committed remediation.
